Title:
Password input accepts invalid passwords that do not meet system requirements

Summary:
User is able to register/login using a password that does not meet the system is requirements (minimum 8 characters, at least one number, and one uppercase letter).

Environment:
Windows 10, Chrome 

Severity: Major
Priority: High (P0)

Steps to Reproduce:

Go to the login/registration page

Enter a valid username in the username field

Enter "password" in the password field

Click the Login/Register button

Expected Result:
The system should display the message:
"Please make sure your password meets the requirements"
and prevent the user from logging in/registering.

Actual Result:
The system allows the user to log in/register with the invalid password and takes the user to the dashboard.
